To calculate ROA (Return on Assets), the formula is:

\[
\text{ROA} = \frac{\text{Net Profit}}{\text{Average Total Assets}} \times 100\%
\]

Step 1: Identify Net Profit from the income statement:
- Net Profit = 1,095,371.35

Step 2: Calculate Average Total Assets from the balance sheet:
- Initial Total Assets (2023-12-31) = 13,000,000.00
- Ending Total Assets (2024-01-27) = 14,823,650.85

\[
\text{Average Total Assets} = \frac{13,000,000.00 + 14,823,650.85}{2} = \frac{27,823,650.85}{2} = 13,911,825.425
\]

Step 3: Calculate ROA:

\[
\text{ROA} = \frac{1,095,371.35}{13,911,825.425} \times 100\% \approx 7.87\%
\]
